Fix this in src/aerolitctl/cli.py, inside add_configure_server_parser().

Look for these two argument blocks:

server_parser.add_argument(
    "--nfs-enabled",
    dest="nfs_enabled",
    action="store_true",
    default=None,
    help="Enable NFS/controller generated settings.",
)
server_parser.add_argument(
    "--no-nfs",
    dest="nfs_enabled",
    action="store_false",
    help="Disable NFS/controller generated settings.",
)

Replace them with:

server_parser.add_argument(
    "--nfs-enabled",
    dest="nfs_enabled",
    action="store_true",
    default=None,
    help="Enable Ansible Controller / NFS generated settings.",
)
server_parser.add_argument(
    "--no-nfs",
    dest="nfs_enabled",
    action="store_false",
    help="Disable Ansible Controller / NFS generated settings.",
)

I’d also fix the guided prompt in src/aerolitctl/server.py so the interactive wording matches.

Find this in choose_nfs_settings():

nfs_enabled = yes_no_prompt(
    "Enable NFS/controller settings?",
    default=current_nfs.get("enabled", True),
)

Replace with:

nfs_enabled = yes_no_prompt(
    "Enable Ansible Controller / NFS settings?",
    default=current_nfs.get("enabled", True),
)

Then run:

python3 -m compileall src
aerolitctl configure server --help

You should now see Ansible Controller / NFS instead of NFS/controller in the configure help.